---
layout: layouts/base.njk
pageClass: page-tools
title: Tools
description: Public tools, utilities, and downloadable assets by Ryan Wheeler.
---
{% set toolTags = collections.tools | collectTerms("tags") %}

<section class="shell page-intro">
  <div>
    <p class="eyebrow">Tools</p>
    <h1>Utilities, assets, and free releases that should be easy to grab.</h1>
  </div>
  <p>
    Categories are data-driven. They only appear when you actually publish something in them.
  </p>
</section>

{% if collections.tools.length %}
  <section class="shell tools-filter-row" data-tool-filter>
    <div class="chip-list">
      <button class="chip-button is-active" type="button" data-tool-filter-value="all">All</button>
      {% for tag in toolTags %}
        <button class="chip-button" type="button" data-tool-filter-value="{{ tag | slugify }}">{{ tag }}</button>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="shell tool-grid" data-tool-grid>
    {% for tool in collections.tools %}
      {% set toolTagsDisplay = tool.data.tags | displayTags %}
      <article class="tool-grid-card" data-tool-item data-tags="{% for tag in toolTagsDisplay %}{{ tag | slugify }}{% if not loop.last %}|{% endif %}{% endfor %}">
        <a href="{{ tool.url }}">
          <img src="{{ tool.data.thumbnail }}" alt="{{ tool.data.title }}">
        </a>
        <div class="tool-grid-copy">
          <h2><a href="{{ tool.url }}">{{ tool.data.title }}</a></h2>
          <p>{{ tool.data.summary }}</p>
          <div class="tag-row">
            {% for tag in toolTagsDisplay %}
              <span class="tag-chip">{{ tag }}</span>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </section>
{% else %}
  <section class="shell empty-state-panel">
    <div class="empty-state-card empty-state-card-wide">
      <p class="eyebrow">Structure first</p>
      <h2>The tools shelf is ready, even before the first batch is filled in.</h2>
      <p>
        This page is built to support Unity tools, downloadable assets, raw files, GitHub releases, and optional dedicated tool pages without another redesign pass.
      </p>
      <p>
        When new tool types appear, their categories will appear automatically from content metadata instead of being pre-baked into the layout.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
{% endif %}

